This paper deals with object pose estimation and categorization from images, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of hierarchical object representation algorithms and the extraction of statistical and geometric features suggest that this paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of optimization algorithms and the joint approach to pose estimation and categorization suggest that this paper also belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on multi-view object pose estimation suggests that this paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of image datasets suggests that this paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
